metadata.name: Merkki #27
metadata.description:
Merkki is an exploration of primitive forms, randomness and bold lines.
Drawing inspiration from mid-70s iconic single-color logotypes, this project revolves heavily around constraints and minimalism.

- 5 different shape types
- 3 grid sizes
- Mostly monochrome, with occasional color accents

Press ‚Äús‚Äù to save a 4000x4000px image.

metadata.name: demonz #94
metadata.description:
Alert!

In a newly explored ancient temple a portal from hell opened and let these 6666 demonz demonize and roam in the human world.
Try to get these demonz on your side to help you survive in this painful hell on earth.

metadata.name: Gestalt #741
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time
‚Ä¢ 'R' reassembles the piece with all elements
‚Ä¢ 'S' saves the output
